name: Jimmy Carter
summary: On October 1, 2023, Jimmy Carter, the 39th President of the United States, became the first former president to reach the milestone age of 100. Despite his declining health, as reported by his grandson, Carter's legacy and impact continue to be celebrated. Commentators have highlighted the lessons to be learned from his presidency, emphasizing his humanitarian efforts and progressive views. Articles have explored his post-presidential work, recognizing his contributions to peacebuilding and public health initiatives. The occasion has also prompted reflections on his personal journey and the enduring relevance of his principles, which inspire others to strive for a better world.

summary: Royal news has been abuzz with the announcement that Princess Beatrice is expecting her second child with husband Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi. name: Thelwall Viaduct
summary: A lorry has crashed off the Thelwall Viaduct on the M6 near Warrington, causing severe traffic delays. The lorry fell 60 meters onto a bank below, but the driver miraculously escaped with minor injuries. The accident occurred during rush hour, leading to significant disruption on the motorway. The M6 was closed in both directions, with only one lane reopened later. An investigation is underway to determine the cause of the accident. The driver was thrown from the bridge during the impact, but police have confirmed they avoided serious injuries.

name: Westminster Academy
summary: A horrific acid attack at Westminster Academy in west London has left a 14-year-old schoolgirl with potentially life-changing injuries. The suspect remains at large, prompting a police manhunt for a "lone" individual riding an e-scooter. The incident has shocked the school community, with pupils and staff also being rushed to the hospital. The suspected acid attack has prompted widespread concern, with authorities seeking the public's assistance in apprehending the attacker. The attack has left the victim with severe injuries, underscoring the need for urgent action to address such heinous acts of violence.

name: Premium Bonds
summary: The National Savings & Investments (NS&I) has announced the winners of their Premium Bonds draw for October 2024. Two millionaires were revealed in Derbyshire and Gloucestershire. One fortunate saver won £100,000 with a £275 holding, highlighting the chance of winning big with even small investments. However, NS&I issued a warning about incorrect account balances, urging customers to check their accounts carefully. Additionally, a report indicated that some Premium Bonds savers might be facing a "£1,400 shortfall" due to an inaccurate reading on their accounts. The names of the £1 million jackpot winners were also announced, generating excitement among participants.
